div.note:
Linguistic analysis by Robert L. Rankin, Kenneth Miner, and John E. Koontz yields the following:
Kháxe paha signifies " Crow head"; " Sar ná no ne" does not mean " Iron Eyes," but no definite translation is possible;
Į̄swe x ą́ ǰe signifies " Big Ax"; I štá grax ą ǰemeans "Very Big Eyes," without reference to the color blue; M įkhe seweapparently means "Black Raccoon," perhaps Clark'sword "cat"; and Wa š ó šeg ǫ may be translated as "Like [a] Brave." Waphíyamay be translated as "He does [what is] Good."
